♪Can they hold one more soul♪

253
00:17:10,131 --> 00:17:13,664
♪I paint my brows
and send mournful melodies♪

254
00:17:14,004 --> 00:17:16,352
♪Let the tale fade♪

255
00:17:16,672 --> 00:17:18,944
♪Mortal world's fireworks in your eyes♪

256
00:17:19,043 --> 00:17:20,256
♪Galaxies sparkle♪

257
00:17:20,372 --> 00:17:22,876
♪Yet by your side, I don't reside♪

258
00:17:23,109 --> 00:17:25,280
♪Only fleeting beauty remains♪

259
00:17:25,664 --> 00:17:29,600
♪I pour and drink in solitude♪

260
00:17:45,336 --> 00:17:48,288
♪The mountains are green,
and the lake is like a mirror♪

261
00:17:48,508 --> 00:17:50,944
♪Oars stir, breaking cloudlike veils♪

262
00:17:51,872 --> 00:17:54,125
♪Carp circle the prow, listening close♪

263
00:17:54,400 --> 00:17:57,440
♪Orioles sing mellifluous refrains♪

264
00:17:58,272 --> 00:18:01,120
♪Lotus stems sway, inspiring verse♪

265
00:18:01,440 --> 00:18:04,192
♪New verses drift with the wind
across the lake♪

266
00:18:04,736 --> 00:18:06,720
♪Parting lotus leaves, I lift my gaze♪

267
00:18:07,104 --> 00:18:09,312
♪In white robes, he rides by slowly♪

268
00:18:10,605 --> 00:18:13,645
♪Grind flesh between grit and stone♪

269
00:18:15,757 --> 00:18:20,077
♪Sink into pain,
only then are pearls born♪

270
00:18:23,469 --> 00:18:27,373
♪Wait until abyssal darkness
stains every inch of skin♪

271
00:18:29,517 --> 00:18:34,573
♪Then comes the time to chase the dawn♪

272
00:18:37,165 --> 00:18:41,773
♪I'll sweep through dusty sands♪

273
00:18:42,381 --> 00:18:45,357
♪Passing wind♪

274
00:18:45,773 --> 00:18:48,973
♪Entwine my hair in dance♪

275
00:18:50,925 --> 00:18:55,405
♪I'll lean into his embrace♪

276
